summary:
The Security Council:

* Emphasizes state capacity-building and coordinated international support for the Haitian Government (para 12);
* Welcomes the deployment of MINUSTAH's maritime patrol boats to support the Haitian National Police's Coast Guard (para 13);
* Requests MINUSTAH to continue patrolling border areas and assessing threats (para 14);
* Calls for complementing security and development operations with activities to improve living conditions (para 15);
* Condemns attacks on MINUSTAH personnel and facilities (para 16);
* Welcomes steps towards reform of rule of law institutions and requests MINUSTAH to provide support (para 17);
* Encourages implementation of the National Prison Administration's strategic plan (para 18);
* Requests MINUSTAH to pursue community violence reduction and support disarmament efforts (para 19);
* Reaffirms MINUSTAH's human rights mandate and calls for promoting and protecting human rights (para 20);
* Strongly condemns grave violations against children and requests MINUSTAH to protect their rights (para 21);
* Requests the Secretary-General to ensure compliance with the zero-tolerance policy on sexual exploitation and abuse (para 22);
* Calls for enhanced coordination between MINUSTAH and the UN country team (para 23);
* Recognizes the need for a high-level donor conference to support Haiti's development plan (para 24);
* Welcomes progress in MINUSTAH's communications and public outreach strategy (para 25);
* Requests the Secretary-General to develop benchmarks to measure progress in Haiti (para 26);
* Requests the Secretary-General to report to the Council semi-annually on MINUSTAH's mandate implementation (para 27);
* Requests a comprehensive assessment of threats to security in Haiti and proposes options to reshape MINUSTAH (para 28);
* Decides to remain seized of the matter (para 29).
